    </collaborator>
  </sponsors>
  <source>Taichung Veterans General Hospital</source>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      To understand if acarbose, an alpha-glucosidase inhibitor usually for treating diabetes, will
      further lower post meal glucose and inflammatory state when taking together with moderate
      amount of alcohol during meal tolerance test in subjects with impaired glucose tolerance or
      mild diabetes.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
